The
Prospectors & Developers Association of Canada’s (PDAC) 2020 Convention—the
world’s premier mineral exploration and mining event—will commence this weekend
in Toronto, marking its 88th year. Every year
the PDAC Convention injects upwards of $70 million into the local Toronto
economy. “The PDAC Convention is the one event the world’s mineral exploration and mining industry cannot afford to miss, and 2020 will be my 32nd consecutive year attending” says PDAC President Felix Lee. “It is an opportunity for industry professionals to gather and best position themselves and their companies for the year ahead.” Read the full press release